<font face="Arial" size="2"><i>Posted by <b><a href="mailto:joe_smoe56@hotmail.com">Windman</a></b> at 2004-09-26 08:41:53</i><br><br>Simple solution to hoarding of dkp points.  <br><br>The first time a highly uber and sought after item drops, assign a high dkp cost. (:Say twice that of what it would normally be:)  When the item drops again lower dkp cost subsequently each time. (:Perhaps a fixed percentage, or changable depending on guild dkp point availability:)<br><br>Perhaps if the item continues to be highly sought after, then dkp remains high. (:Risky. because it may seem unfair. perhaps make an initial test of this secondary system:)<br><br>This Primary System would:<br>1. Reward those that have saved their dkp, by allowing them first dibs on an item as they have the most purchasing power.<br>2. By lessoning the amount of dkp needed for purchase it will cause others w/hoarded dkp to pay alot, but still give those w/the most first choice.  <br><br>In conclusion, by assigning high dkp cost for uber first drop item and then lessoning sequencially it rewards those w/ alot of dkp to have first dibs, but lessons their dkp stores more so than those who have less dkp who purchase that same item, or other such items in the future.  It will also make it more fair for those on the lower end.  The people with high dkp will not be able to double up slots w/highly wanted items.  eventually allowing people with less dkp to get the item. This system also allows for a more evenly distribution of items, giving the guild better overall strength.<br><br>Feel free to contact me at joe_smoe56@hotmail.com if you comments, suggestions, or would like to debate this issue.<br><br>later-<br>windman <br>
